review_blob: At brewpubone of our favorites of the flights. Interesting blend. Dark brown pour. Big cherry, slightly vinous, definitely sour, toffee malts, even some Christmas spices. But nicely balanced and drank great for the ABV. Great stuff from Wrecking Bar.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Humdinger Old Stock Ale

review_blob: At brewpubreally loved this strange saison. It really was all over the place, but it worked. Had citrus and spice and a earthy body. The rye and the Belgian yeast was in there as well. It had tartness balanced with the rye that made it taste almost like a gose. Just a fun different beer.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Partition Rustic Urban Ale

review_blob: Cloudy straw with pillowy white head. Petrichor aroma, like the smell of rain on a Spring evening. A shortening bread body, delicately spiced. The coriander and orange peel and pineapple meander among the strong Belgian presence, a terroir of Tennessee Hill Country in its dry earthy finish. Crisp body. A hand crafted spiritous character, harkening to the white lightning roots of the region. -review by the wife

A dark red-brown pour. Red wine and cherry in the aroma. The taste brought more of the barreling and slight tart presence. I wonder what all the wild ales that were blended with this, because it does have an interesting taste. Pretty sticky and sweet for a sour. Still nice to try.
Big fruity smell. Lots of apricot. The saltiness and tartness are there, but not as prevalent as the tropical-ness. Even if a little unbalanced, it still was a crisp light great summer beer.
Nice Strong Brown. Deep mahagony color. Coffee definitely popped in taste and aroma. New mild coffee. Definitely had some chocolate and even toffee notes. Very smooth at 9% Good stuff.
Pretty solid pils actually. The sweet orange helps with the hay dominated body. Easy drinking.
At brewpub. Solid pale ale that definitely leaned towards a fruity, citrusy hop palate. Easy drinkin'
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Mandarina Bavaria Pale Ale

review_blob: At BHB depot fest...big black pour. Coffee, chocolate, licorice, pitted fruit, mild booze. Pretty good stuff!
beer_name: Against the Grain / Dry & Bitter Your Lytest One

review_blob: At BHB Depot Festa fairly doughy type beer that definitely had some tropical and guava presence. Drinkable and pretty tasty.
beer_name: Cherry Street Groovy Child Dry Hopped Guava Ale

review_blob: At BHB Depot Festyeah, pretty much a chocolate coffee and light coconut porter. I dont remember much vanilla or date taste, but, hey, I believe theyre in there.
beer_name: Cherry Street Chief Sawnees Stash Coconut Porter

review_blob: At BHB Depot Festcool concept I thought and relatively successful as I did get the malt-caramel from Irish red and the applely-Belgian wit. They were relatively balanced, and certainly interesting tasting.
beer_name: Southern Sky Worlds Apart Pink Ale

review_blob: At BHB Depot Festgood lawnmower type beer. Just straight down the middle golden corny blonde with pretty hefty bitter finish.

At BHB Depot Festdefinitely had a woody, oaky character that made the tripel seem sort of tart. Some cherry, dark fruit. Lots of alcohol burn. Still not bad at all, even if kind of all over the place.

At BHB Depot Fest.interesting beer. It definitely was a lot of wine and oak character for the barreling. The saison barely popped through, mostly with Belgian spice. Brett was definitely in the mix too. All over the place, but kind of fun beer.

Dark golden color. Spices really dominate aroma, the chamomile is definitely the heavy hitter. The taste is a earthy and lemony, giving a weird herbal presence that doesnt play especially well with the wheat. Light and sessionable enough. Okay.
Fun gose. Bright red color. Cherry and salt and a touch of funk and tart. A little on the sweet sticky side but still Super easy drinker
Thanks Danny! Awesome balanced DIPA. Equally sweet and bitter. Grapefruit, tropical, and earth. Bright, not too sticky. Good stuff
beer_name: Wicked Weed Freak Of Nature Double IPA

review_blob: Thanks Danny! Fantastic ba imperial. Viscous black pour. Vanilla, dark fruits, coconut, spice, chocolate and of course a sweet bourbon. More lively tasting than some imperial stouts. Great stuff.
beer_name: Wicked Weed Dark Age Bourbon Stout

review_blob: First rater! At BHB train depot fest.not the best looking beer. a bit like swamp water. Tasted pretty good. Creamy, chocolate, maybe a bit of hazlenutty. Pretty sweet. Decent
beer_name: Southern Sky Golden Ticket Milk Chocolate Stout

review_blob: First raterat BHB Depot festI liked the idea, but didnt quite land. Very sweet and artificial blueberry. Had the dubbel body and with the maple addition and blueberries became a bit cloying. Still a fun beer to try.
beer_name: Southern Sky Hot Southern Blueberry Hoecake Ale

review_blob: Solid hybrid at brewpub. Good balance between sweet malts, citrus hops, roasty malts, and spicy rye. Balanced and doesnt go too far in any direction. Wrecking bar makes some good beer.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Hopback Mountain Imperial Rye India Black Ale

review_blob: At brewpubsilly name, YOGURT!, but good beer. Nice chocolate and roasty coffee body with a hop kick. Not your usual schwarzbier. Super smooth and drinkable.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar May The Schwarzbier With You

review_blob: At brewpubthis beer was fantastic. Citrus aroma bounced off the glass. It has a great complex balance between tropical, citrus, pit fruit, and pine. Perfect medium body. Awesome.
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Dis Juice Pale Ale

review_blob: Old ratingsweet stout that seems like it has been watered down. Brown sugar, chocolate, malts.just too thin and milk-toast.
Down the middle imperial stout. Chocolate, black licorice, dark fruits, decent amount of bitterness. Medium bodied. Okay.
beer_name: Starr Hill All Access Cryptical Imperial Stout

review_blob: Nice gose, but nothing particularly fantastic. It does have a bit of a melon and sea salt aroma. And definitely a melon in the taste, but did not have the huge tart presence. More jolly rancher sweet fruit. Still easy drinking.
Decent enough Imperial Stout. Black pour. Was a little thinner than I excepted and a big herbal/anise presence. It did have a nice coffee-chocolate base. Okay.
beer_name: The Duck-Rabbit Rabid Duck Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Solid amberor ESB-thing. Murky amber colored. Malt sweetness hits upfront but has a nice sharp bitter finish. Balanced between the two. Good stuff.
Thanks Danny! Pretty fantastic pale ale. Nice golden clear color. Dank, fruity, somewhat grassy. Crisp, clean, and blended well. Could drink all day. Bonus points for the chess-centered label.
Yup, Minty coffee earthy porter. Everything solidly balanced. Medium body. Nothing to go over the moon but it delivers.
beer_name: Ballast Point Victory at Sea - Peppermint

review_blob: At BHB depot fest... solid black IPA that was more pale malts and chocolate than hops. Nice bitter finish. Pretty decent.
At BHB depot fest...pretty solid Porter. Some roast, coffee, cocoa. Dry finish, clean.
At BHB depot fest...kind of a generic session IPA. Lighter, nothing especially off that I can remember but didn't pop in any way.
At BHB depot fest. Nice heavily citrus session. Big fruity, pineapple, tropical as expected. Clean finish. One of the red hares I liked more.
First rater! At BHB depot fest, really nice clean very fruity and orangey IPA. Bright orange color. Bit sweet, but tasty IPA.
At BHB depot fest...nice wit. Nothing super special , didn't get much of the white oak, but still a light doughy drinkable wit.
At BHB Depot Fest...pretty good amber. Bready, sweet, but with good rye spice and some oakiness. Drinkable and a nice departure.
A bottle at the Local in Tifton...not my favorite style, but this one was weird...some hay and fruitiness. just not super clean tasting. not offensive, but not something id try again
At Wrecking Bar Brewpub, the barrel was way heavy in this one and not particularly balanced well. Still a fine beer, but huge bourbon and vanilla dwarf the scotch ale aspects.
beer_name: Monday Night Bourbon Barrel Drafty Kilt

review_blob: At BHB fest.nice treatment. Cinnamon and additional chocolate presence bend well with the solid malty scotch ale base. Nice spice and sweetness kick.
beer_name: Monday Night Drafty Kilt Cinnamon Cocoa

review_blob: At BHB depot fest... Great imperial stout, cool idea. Coffee nutty chocolate, booze burn. Solid, all around.
At BHB depot fest...nice super dank IPA. Bright citrus and huge dank body. Nice punchy DIPA.

At BHB Depot festmaybe our groups favorite of the day. A mighty beer, that ironically we got multiple pours of while people were standing waiting for huny. Big bold across the board, huge chocolate and coffee, nice bourbon and vanilla, the peppers were definitely there, but acted to cut some of the sweetness. It was intense. Fantastic.
beer_name: Burnt Hickory Kolbs Farm (The Burial Truce)

review_blob: At BHB depot festjust a damn good stout. Complexgot plenty of chocolate, coffee, honey, fudge, dark fruit, bourbon, booze burn. Sweet, but not cloying. Boozy, but not hard to drink. Yes!

At BHB Depot festhad some higher hopes for this one. The premise is awesome. It came out as just an okay beer.Vanilla, spice, ginger, some vegetal aspects, Belgian. Just didnt have the sweet and savory that carrot cake makes you think of. Glad I got to try it though.
At BHB Depot Fest.interesting IPA. Definitely was extremely fruit and sweet. Definitely got the candy sugar aspect. A bit earthy as well.
beer_name: Three Taverns / Burnt Hickory A Night On Moon Station IPA

review_blob: At BHB festloved it, what an awesome session-ish fun beer. Mango brightens and slight jalapeo heat gives some mouthfeel to an already very nicely bitter pale ale. Could drink this all the time.
At BHB depot festnice orangsicle beer. Ive had several beers attempt this flavor, I think this was the most successful in keeping the bright citrus and blending creamy, vanilla aspect. Awesome.
At BHB depot festugh, fake chocolate taste took away from the bright orange flavor of the didjits. Not undrinkable, but not great especially in light of their other stuff that day.
beer_name: Burnt Hickory The Didjits (Judge Hot Fudge)
